I'd be fine adding a method to ExecutableOutput called throwOnNonZeroExitCode(String message) so that
`
ExecutableOutput output = executableRunner.execute(directory, goExe, arguments);
    if (output.getReturnCode() == 0) {
        return output.getStandardOutputAsList();
    } else {
        throw new DetectableException(failureMessage + output.getReturnCode());
    }

would become 
ExecutableOutput output = executableRunner.execute(directory, goExe, arguments);
output.throwOnNonZeroExitCode(failureMessage);
return output.getStandardOutputAsList();
`
And if that's the only thing in this class, I have no problem with GoListUJsonGenerator and GoModGraphTransformer both having a method like this. In reality I think only GoListUJsonGenerator would benefit from putting that code in a method.

